# Festag — popup header (stacked H1)

Popups use a **large stacked headline**. Put the explanation in the H1 (max two lines). Do **not** add a small subtitle / T1 under the title.

## Do

```tsx
<h2 className="festag-modal-title festag-modal-title--stacked">
  <span className="festag-modal-title-line">Support kontaktieren</span>
  <span className="festag-modal-title-line festag-modal-title-line--muted">
    Beschreiben Sie Ihr Anliegen — wir melden uns schnellstmöglich.
  </span>
</h2>
```

Or pass `title` + `subtitle` to `Modal` — they render as stacked H1 lines (subtitle is muted, still H1-sized).

- **Light:** muted line `#8891a0` / `--fp-muted`
- **Dark / OLED:** muted `rgba(245,245,247,0.68)` / `--fp-muted`

## Don't

- Small muted paragraph under the title as a separate T1
- Incomplete half-sentences or question fragments as the second line
- Page `h1` leads — those stay forbidden (`festag-no-page-leads`)

## Body

Fields and actions follow the global form / button system. Extra body copy only when needed for lists, notes, or errors — not as a duplicate of the H1 explanation.
